-- IDFC Seeks Fund Management Investor for Asset Management Unit, ET Reports
-- Madelene Pearson
-- 2010-06-21T02:00:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-21/idfc-seeks-fund-management-investor-for-asset-management-unit-et-reports.html

          
          
             Infrastructure Development Finance
Co. Ltd. plans to take a global fund manager as a strategic
partner in its asset management unit, India’s Economic Times
reported, citing the company’s executive director Vicar Lemay.  
 IDFC is looking at a strategic partnership to either manage
the fund, or advise on foreign flow of funds into the Indian
equity market, the newspaper said, citing the executive.  
